  "title": "Manufacturing & Logistic Coordinator",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Opening: Logistics & Production Coordinator</strong></p><p><strong>Location:</strong> Kallang, Central Singapore<br /><strong>Employment Type:</strong> Full-time<br /><strong>Availability</strong> :<strong> IMMEDIATE</strong></p><h3><strong>Company Description: </strong></h3><p>This company is an established private-label manufacturing company specializing in the beauty and cosmetics industry. We have been delivering high-quality products since 1990. Our success is a result of our continuous investment in human capital and innovation, setting us apart from other manufacturers in the industry<strong>.</strong></p><h3><strong>About the Role</strong></h3><p>We are looking for a reliable and hands-on <strong>Logistics & Production Coordinator</strong> to support our daily production and logistics operations. This role is suited for someone who is physically fit, detail-oriented, and able to work well in a team-based environment.   <br /><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Set up, operate, and monitor machinery and basic equipment for production tasks.</li><li>Inspect, assemble, package, and label finished products according to specifications.</li><li>Maintain accurate records of inventory, production output, and deliveries.</li><li>Follow all company safety guidelines, hygiene policies, and Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs).</li><li>Coordinate with the administrative and production teams to ensure timely stock availability for production.</li><li>Assist the Quality Control (QC) team with the inspection and release of finished goods.</li><li>Manage incoming and outgoing shipments, including storage, handling, and delivery of goods (Class 3 driving licence required).</li><li>Perform loading, unloading, and internal movement of goods within the warehouse or worksite.</li></ul><h3><strong>Requirements</strong></h3><p>- Possess a valid Class 3 Driving License.</p><p>- Willingness to learn to operate equipment used in operation and warehouse (e.g. pallet jet, basic machinery).</p><p>- Responsible, punctual, and a strong team player.</p><p>- Able to manage multiple tasks in a fast-paced environment.</p><p>- Good attention to detail and good communication skills.</p><p>- Able to understand and comply with work instructions and safety guidelines.<br /><br />- Physically fit and able to perform manual lifting.</p><p><strong></strong><br /><u>Other Details</u><br />- Working location: Kallang Basin Industrial Estate (nearest MRT: DTL Bendemeer/ EW Lavender)<br />- Working hours: 5 days, 8am-5pm Mon-Fri<br />- Salary package: Basic salary + OT + AWS + VB (subject to performance)<br />- Annual contract subject to probation</p>",
